Initial reception date 02Feb16: This solicited report received from a health care professional representing a 
distributor concerned a 11-year-old male patient with lipidosis was hospitalized on an unreported date due to 
meningitis during the use of Zavesca (miglustat).  Medical history was not reported. Concomitant medications 
included modafinil, paracetamol and piroxicam. Zavesca 100 mg three times day was started on 22Jan13 and 
remains ongoing.
Outcome was reported as unknown. A causality assessment was not provided.
Company comment: It is Actelion policy for solicited reports from non-interventional programs received with 
reporter's causality unstated (missing) or unknown to provide a conservative causality assessment of "suspected" 
for reporting purposes until the causality is clarified with the reporter.
